      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GO COLOUR MY WORLD NZ (6) led from this barrier at Wagga last start and went on to record a dominant win by more 7 metres. That gave him three wins, along with a very close second, from his last five starts. Can add to that strong form line. BEYOND DOUBT NZ (8) last appeared when fifth at Albion Park four-and-a-half months ago and won two of his previous three Brisbane starts. Proven fresh and won his lone attempt at this distance. Draws wide but was readied with a trial placing. SLYX NZ (11) led and kept going to score by close to 5 metres at Penrith last start, the second win from his past four appearances. Hard to know where he gets to from this second row draw but he tends to do his best work at this distance and is racing well. BETTORS HOPE (10) may need luck from this draw but wasn't too far away from the placegetters in stronger company last start.",
